.TH "kstat_irqs_usr" 9 "kstat_irqs_usr" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
kstat_irqs_usr \- Get the statistics for an interrupt from thread context
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "unsigned int" kstat_irqs_usr
.BI "(unsigned int irq "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "irq" 12
The interrupt number
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Returns the sum of interrupt counts on all cpus since boot for \fIirq\fP.

It uses rcu to protect the access since a concurrent removal of an
interrupt descriptor is observing an rcu grace period before
\fBdelayed_free_desc\fP/\fBirq_kobj_release\fP.
